. 
<typeStatus id="367E96CE195B587421003F22A2E3F77E" box="[347,389,1351,1370]" pageId="23" pageNumber="280">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF195B5874218F3F22A1B4F77E" authority="Baly, 1858" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1858" box="[468,722,1351,1370]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Homalispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batesii">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E195B5874218F3F22A116F77E" box="[468,624,1351,1370]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="280">Homalispa batesii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8D54559D195B5874222E3F22A1B4F77E" author="BALY J. S." box="[629,722,1351,1370]" pageId="23" pageNumber="280" refId="ref28592" refString="BALY J. S. 1858: Catalogue of Hispidae in the collection of the British Museum. Part I. Order of the Trustees, London, 172 pp. + 9 pls." type="book" year="1858">Baly, 1858</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by original designation.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97A286C195B5874202A3F17A04AF44D" blockId="23.[113,1089,1394,1641]" pageId="23" pageNumber="280">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E195B5874202A3F17A2FDF7AD" bold="true" box="[113,411,1394,1417]" pageId="23" pageNumber="280">Distinguishing characters.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF195B587421FB3F17A173F7AD" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1858" box="[416,533,1394,1417]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Homalispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E195B587421FB3F17A173F7AD" box="[416,533,1394,1417]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="280">Homalispa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be easily distinguished from other genera by the prognathous and projecting mouthparts, and the long antennae which are about 1.5 times longer than the base of the pronotum (
<figureCitation id="71FE34E9195B587422553FD7A128F7ED" box="[526,590,1458,1481]" captionStart="Figs 1–11" captionStartId="8.[151,188,1381,1400]" captionTargetBox="[175,1099,219,1316]" captionTargetId="figure-10@8.[174,1104,219,1322]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 1–11. Dorsal habitus. 1 – Homalispa batesii Baly, 1858, French Guyana: Mt. Kaw; 2 – Cyclantispa gracilis (Baly, 1885), Panama: La Fortuna; 3 –Xanthispa cimicoides (Guérin-Méneville, 1844), French Guyana: Le Larivot; 4 – Imatidium thoracicum Fabricius, 1801, Ecuador: Cascada San Rafael; 5 – Aslamidium (s. str.) capense (Herbst, 1799), French Guyana: Fourgassie; 6 – Aslamidium (Neoaslamidium) pichinchaensis Borowiec, 1998, Ecuador: Puerto Misahuallí; 7 – Calliaspis sachaensis Borowiec &amp; Stojczew, 1998, Ecuador: Shushu¿ndi; 8 – Spaethaspis lloydi Hincks, 1952, Ecuador: Río Puno. 9 – Xenispa testaceicornis (Pic, 1926), Bolivia: Refugio Los Volcanes; 10 – Xenispa costaricensis (Uhmann, 1930), Panama:La Fortuna;11 – Euxema insignis Baly, 1858, syntype, Panama: Volcan de Barú. All scale bars = 2.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301734" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301734/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="280">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). The other two genera, 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF195B587423033FD7A0B1F7ED" authority="Sekerka, 2014" authorityName="Sekerka" authorityYear="2014" box="[856,983,1458,1481]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cyclantispa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E195B587423033FD7A0B1F7ED" box="[856,983,1458,1481]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="280">Cyclantispa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="C0824905195B587423843FD7A727F7ED" box="[991,1089,1458,1481]" pageId="23" pageNumber="280" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF195B587420C53FB7A26CF7CD" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1858" box="[158,266,1490,1513]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Xanthispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E195B587420C53FB7A26CF7CD" box="[158,266,1490,1513]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="280">Xanthispa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with strongly projecting mouthparts differ in having much shorter antennae, approximately as long as the pronotal base and the pronotum without an emargination above the head and with obtuse and non-projecting anterior corners, while 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF195B5874232C3C77A08AF40D" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1858" box="[887,1004,1554,1577]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Homalispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E195B5874232C3C77A08AF40D" box="[887,1004,1554,1577]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="280">Homalispa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the antennae at least 1.5 times longer than the pronotal base and the pronotum deeply emarginate above the head and with angulate and projecting anterior corners.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A1DF7BE71954587B20CC3AB9A18BF0D7" pageId="24" pageNumber="281" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="E97A286C1954587B20CC3AB9A2C6F317" blockId="24.[151,1127,220,979]" pageId="24" pageNumber="281">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E1954587B20CC3AB9A260F2D7" bold="true" box="[151,262,220,243]" pageId="24" pageNumber="281">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8D54559D1954587B21503AB9A177F2D7" author="MONROS F. &amp; VIANA M. J." box="[267,529,220,243]" pageId="24" pageNumber="281" pagination="125 - 324" refId="ref30821" refString="MONROS F. &amp; VIANA M. J. 1947: Revision sistematica de los Hispidae argentinos (Insecta, Coleopt. Chrysomeloid.). Annales del Museo Argentino de Ciencias Naturales Bernardino Rivadavia 42: 125 - 324 + 27 pls." type="journal article" year="1947">MONRÓS &amp; VIANA (1947)</bibRefCitation>
designated 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF1954587B22D43AB9A096F2D7" authority="Baly, 1858" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1858" box="[655,1008,220,243]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Homalispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginata">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E1954587B22D43AB9A01EF2D7" box="[655,888,220,243]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="281">Homalispa marginata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8D54559D1954587B23253AB9A096F2D7" author="BALY J. S." box="[894,1008,220,243]" pageId="24" pageNumber="281" refId="ref28592" refString="BALY J. S. 1858: Catalogue of Hispidae in the collection of the British Museum. Part I. Order of the Trustees, London, 172 pp. + 9 pls." type="book" year="1858">Baly, 1858</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as the 
<typeStatus id="367E96CE1954587B24623AB9A701F2D7" box="[1081,1127,220,243]" pageId="24" pageNumber="281">type</typeStatus>
species, however, this designation is invalid as the 
<typeStatus id="367E96CE1954587B22973A99A19CF337" box="[716,762,252,275]" pageId="24" pageNumber="281">type</typeStatus>
species was ¿xed in the original description (
<bibRefCitation id="8D54559D1954587B21463B79A2F5F317" author="BALY J. S." box="[285,403,284,307]" pageId="24" pageNumber="281" refId="ref28592" refString="BALY J. S. 1858: Catalogue of Hispidae in the collection of the British Museum. Part I. Order of the Trustees, London, 172 pp. + 9 pls." type="book" year="1858">BALY 1858</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97A286C1954587B20EE3B59A098F397" blockId="24.[151,1127,220,979]" pageId="24" pageNumber="281">
In the past, 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF1954587B216C3B59A2CAF377" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1858" box="[311,428,316,339]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Homalispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E1954587B216C3B59A2CAF377" box="[311,428,316,339]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="281">Homalispa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was divided in two subgenera: the nominotypical subgenus and 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF1954587B20CC3B39A262F357" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1858" box="[151,260,348,371]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Xanthispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E1954587B20CC3B39A262F357" box="[151,260,348,371]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="281">Xanthispa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(i.e. 
<bibRefCitation id="8D54559D1954587B21183B39A28AF357" author="UHMANN E." box="[323,492,348,371]" pageId="24" pageNumber="281" pagination="1 - 153" refId="ref32155" refString="UHMANN E. 1957 a: Chrysomelidae: Hispinae. Hispinae Americanae. In: HINCKS W. D. (ed.): Coleopterorum Catalogus Supplementa, Pars 35, Fasc. 1. Dr. W. Junk, ' s-Gravenhage, pp. i - vii + 1 - 153." type="book chapter" year="1957">UHMANN 1957a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="8D54559D1954587B21A03B39A1F6F357" author="STAINES C. L." box="[507,656,348,371]" pageId="24" pageNumber="281" pagination="721 - 784" refId="ref31494" refString="STAINES C. L. 2002: The New World tribes and genera of Hispines (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washinghton 104: 721 - 784." type="journal article" year="2002">STAINES 2002</bibRefCitation>
). However, in my opinion, 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF1954587B239C3B39A752F357" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1858" box="[967,1076,348,371]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Xanthispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E1954587B239C3B39A752F357" box="[967,1076,348,371]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="281">Xanthispa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a distinct genus and its status is restored here. In addition, two species previously classi¿ed as 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF1954587B20CC3BF9A26AF397" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1858" box="[151,268,412,435]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Homalispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E1954587B20CC3BF9A26AF397" box="[151,268,412,435]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="281">Homalispa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF1954587B218B3BF9A129F397" authority="Sekerka, 2014" authorityName="Sekerka" authorityYear="2014" box="[464,591,412,435]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cyclantispa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E1954587B218B3BF9A129F397" box="[464,591,412,435]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="281">Cyclantispa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="C08249051954587B220D3BF9A1D1F397" box="[598,695,412,435]" pageId="24" pageNumber="281" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(see description on page 274).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97A286C1954587B20EE3BD9A18CF057" blockId="24.[151,1127,220,979]" pageId="24" pageNumber="281">
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF1954587B20EE3BD9A293F3F7" authority="Pic, 1926" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1926" box="[181,501,444,467]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Homalispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="signata">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E1954587B20EE3BD9A2E2F3F7" box="[181,388,444,467]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="281">Homalispa signata</emphasis>
Pic, 1926
</taxonomicName>
is considered as a species of 
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E1954587B231D3BD9A0BBF3F7" box="[838,989,444,467]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="281">incertae sedis</emphasis>
because the 
<typeStatus id="367E96CE1954587B20CC3BB9A392F3D7" box="[151,244,476,499]" pageId="24" pageNumber="281">holotype</typeStatus>
deposited in MNHN was damaged by pests and is missing the head and part of the pronotum, thus its assignment to a genus is impossible. 
<bibRefCitation id="8D54559D1954587B22A03B99A01FF037" author="PIC M." box="[763,889,508,531]" pageId="24" pageNumber="281" pagination="1 - 32" refId="ref30898" refString="PIC M. 1926 b: Nouveautes diverses. Melanges Exotico-Entomologiques 47: 1 - 32." type="journal article" year="1926">PIC (1926b)</bibRefCitation>
