<subSubSection id="A1DF7BE71954587B20CC3979A144F197" pageId="24" pageNumber="281" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="E97A286C1954587B20CC3979A144F197" blockId="24.[151,1127,220,979]" pageId="24" pageNumber="281">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E1954587B20CC3979A395F117" bold="true" box="[151,243,796,819]" pageId="24" pageNumber="281">Biology.</emphasis>
So far, only two 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF1954587B21EB3979A11CF117" box="[432,634,796,819]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Homalispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E1954587B21EB3979A143F117" box="[432,549,796,819]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="281">Homalispa</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
have published associations with host plants. 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF1954587B20CC3959A288F177" authority="Baly, 1858" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1858" box="[151,494,828,851]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Homalispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deyrollei">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E1954587B20CC3959A214F177" box="[151,370,828,851]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="281">Homalispa deyrollei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8D54559D1954587B21213959A288F177" author="BALY J. S." box="[378,494,828,851]" pageId="24" pageNumber="281" refId="ref28592" refString="BALY J. S. 1858: Catalogue of Hispidae in the collection of the British Museum. Part I. Order of the Trustees, London, 172 pp. + 9 pls." type="book" year="1858">Baly, 1858</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was recorded from 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF1954587B22933959A0ADF177" authority="(BONDAR 1938)" baseAuthorityName="BONDAR" baseAuthorityYear="1938" box="[712,971,828,851]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="24" pageNumber="281" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">
Poaceae (
<bibRefCitation id="8D54559D1954587B236B3959A0A2F177" author="BONDAR G." box="[816,964,828,851]" pageId="24" pageNumber="281" pagination="15 - 24" refId="ref28856" refString="BONDAR G. 1938: Notas entomologicas da Bahia II. Revista de Entomologia 8: 15 - 24." type="journal article" year="1938">BONDAR 1938</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF1954587B245A3959A218F157" authority="Uhmann, 1930" authorityName="Uhmann" authorityYear="1930" baseAuthorityName="Sekerka" baseAuthorityYear="1930" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Demotispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nevermanni">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E1954587B245A3959A3BCF157" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="281">H. nevermanni</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8D54559D1954587B20BB3939A218F157" author="UHMANN E." box="[224,382,860,883]" pageId="24" pageNumber="281" pagination="209 - 256" refId="ref31852" refString="UHMANN E. 1930: Hispinen aus Costa Rica aus der Ausbeute des Herrn Ferd. Nevermann. 20. Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Hispinen (Col. Chrys.). Folia Zoologica et Hydrobiologica 1: 209 - 256." type="journal article" year="1930">Uhmann, 1930</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF1954587B21E63939A070F157" authority="(MESKINS et al. 2008)" baseAuthorityName="MESKINS" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[445,790,860,883]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="24" pageNumber="281" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">
Arecaceae (
<bibRefCitation id="8D54559D1954587B22613939A068F157" author="MESKINS C. &amp; WINDSOR D. &amp; HANCE T." box="[570,782,860,883]" pageId="24" pageNumber="281" pagination="159 - 171" refId="ref30750" refString="MESKINS C., WINDSOR D. &amp; HANCE T. 2008: A comparison of hispine beetles (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae) associated with three orders of monocot host plants in lowland Panama. International Journal of Tropical Insect Science 27: 159 - 171." type="journal article" year="2008">MESKINS et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Our ¿eld observations indicate that both associations are correct as we found a number of species on these two plant families (Windsor &amp; Sekerka, unpunbl. data).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
